# Project npm/pnpm config.
#
# NOTE: podframes depends on freshly-published versions of fast-moving SDKs
# (@google/genai, @speech-sdk/core, hyperframes, next, react). If your global
# pnpm config sets a `minimumReleaseAge` supply-chain delay, install will fail
# until those releases age past the threshold.
#
# To unblock, EITHER wait out the delay, OR (preferred) surgically allow just
# these trusted publishers by uncommenting the lines below — this keeps the
# release-age protection on for every other dependency:
#
# minimum-release-age-exclude[]=@google/genai
# minimum-release-age-exclude[]=@speech-sdk/core
# minimum-release-age-exclude[]=hyperframes
# minimum-release-age-exclude[]=next
# minimum-release-age-exclude[]=react
# minimum-release-age-exclude[]=react-dom
